<item>
            <title>[FLINK-15241] Revert the unexpected change of the configuration for Mesos CPU cores</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-15241</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Before 1.10, the default config of cpu cores for Mesos Workers is equal to taskmanager.numberOfTaskSlots. However, it is now 0.0 by default. I feel sorry I&apos;ve not catch it in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-15196&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;FLINK-15196&lt;/a&gt;. I think this change is unexpected to user thus we need to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=trohrmann&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;trohrmann&quot;&gt;trohrmann&lt;/a&gt; Could you assigned this ticket to me?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
